			<sumFormula>Not provided</sumFormula>
			<common:generalComment xml:lang="en">Sulfate is a significant component in the mineralizing fluids of some world-class rare earth element (REE) deposits. The generation of sulfate-rich hydrothermal fluids is closely associated with the formation of many important ore deposits, such as hydrothermal REE deposits. The transport of REEs in these fluids is complex. REE resources are mainly associated with four geological environments: alkaline igneous rocks, carbonatites, placer deposits with monazite-xenotime mineralisation and ion-adsorption clay deposits.</common:generalComment>
			<common:generalComment xml:lang="zh">硫酸盐是一些世界级稀土元素（REE）矿床成矿流体中的重要成分。富含硫酸盐的热液的生成与许多重要矿床（如热液稀土元素矿床）的形成密切相关。REE 在这些流体中的迁移非常复杂。REE 资源主要与四种地质环境有关：碱性火成岩、碳酸盐岩、含独居石-氙成矿的块状矿床和离子吸附粘土矿床。</common:generalComment>
